      • initCOM

        public static void initCOM()
        Initializes COM library and sets security to impersonate the local user

      • unInitCOM

        public static void unInitCOM()
        UnInitializes COM library if it was initialized by the initCOM() method. Otherwise, does nothing.

      • isComInitialized

        public static boolean isComInitialized()
        COM may already have been initialized outside this class. This boolean is a flag whether this class initialized it, to avoid uninitializing later and killing the external initialization
        Returns:
        Returns whether this class initialized COM

      • isSecurityInitialized

        public static boolean isSecurityInitialized()
        Security only needs to be initialized once. This boolean identifies whether that has happened.
        Returns:
        Returns the securityInitialized.

      • getWmiTimeout

        public static int getWmiTimeout()
        Gets the current WMI timeout. WMI queries will fail if they take longer than this number of milliseconds. A value of -1 is infinite (no timeout).
        Returns:
        Returns the current value of wmiTimeout.

      • setWmiTimeout

        public static void setWmiTimeout(int wmiTimeout)
        Sets the WMI timeout. WMI queries will fail if they take longer than this number of milliseconds.
        Parameters:
        wmiTimeout - The wmiTimeout to set, in milliseconds. To disable timeouts, set timeout as -1 (infinite).
